public enum DigraphProperty
extends java.lang.Enum<DigraphProperty>

A set of properties which may or may not hold for a given digraph.

Enum Constant Summary
AntiSymmetric
          The graph contains no edge (v,u) such that there is an edge (u,v).
CycleFree
          The graph contains no paths from a vertex to that same vertex.
Forest
          Same as Tree, but more than one vertex may have no incoming edges.
LoopFree
          The contains no edges (u,u) for any vertex u.
MultiEdgeFree
          There is at most one edge between every pair of vertices.
Planar
          There exists a function f mapping vertices in the graph to points in a plan such that for every pair of edges (u,v),(u',v') in the graph, the line segments going from f(u) to f(v), and from f(u') to f(v') do not cross.
Symmetric
          For every edge (u,v) in the graph, there exists an edge (v,u) in the graph.
Tree
          Every vertex in the graph except one has exactly one incoming edge.
